-- Sauber F1 Team Signs Hulkenberg as Racing Driver for Next Season
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-10-31T10:58:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-31/sauber-f1-team-signs-hulkenberg-as-racing-driver-for-next-season.html
The Sauber Formula One team said it
signed Germany’s  Nico Hulkenberg  as one of its two racing
drivers for the 2013 season.  The 25-year-old is 12th in the standings with 49 points,
five more than Force India teammate Paul di Resta. He first
raced in the series with Williams in 2010.  Sauber’s Sergio Perez, who leads teammate Kamui Kobayashi,
is moving to McLaren next season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alex Duff at 
 aduff4@bloomberg.net  